In the original pen, there is a space between slashes. So when the user deletes a space, we can check if the last character is a &quot;/&quot; and the deletes the character before that. 

In your case there is no space. At any point, your change listener gets called with a last character as number. 

So you can&#39;t use this approach. In this case I would suggest, track previous value and use it to delete a character before &quot;/&quot;.

